// Repository-specific rules for Cursor AI

// Stack
Use Node.js with ESM (import/export). Prefer TypeScript; use plain JS only where examples already do.
For HTTP servers, prefer Hono over Express.

// Imports
Resolve dependencies through package.json (and workspace links if used). Do not use https:// or http:// URL imports in app or library code.

// Project layout
Keep work under packages/: examples (static / in-browser demos), example-apps (standalone app servers), dev (local dev server and tooling), async-framework (core), custom-element-signals (signals and web component helpers). Add new examples or apps in the matching folder.

// Code style
Preserve existing comments. Prefer const when values are not reassigned. Use async/await for async work and handle errors where it matters.

// Custom elements
Use kebab-case names, extend HTMLElement, and put setup in connectedCallback.

// Testing and quality
Add or extend tests when behavior changes. Run the project test command before committing.

// async-framework package
Put a short "Why:" comment above each public method or non-obvious API to explain its purpose.

// Docs and READMEs
Explain complex logic in comments. Update READMEs when behavior or setup changes. Do not wrap README code samples in backticks unless they already use them.

// Git
Small, focused commits; use feature branches for larger work.

// Maintenance
Update this file when project conventions change.
